data.enText: to bring food from the stomach back out through the mouth
The smell made her want to vomit.

data.chText: 他把晚饭吃的东西都吐了出来。
data.enText: He had vomited up his supper.
The injured man was vomiting blood.
food from the stomach brought back out through the mouth

tr: the reflex act of ejecting the contents of the stomach through the mouth
a medicine that induces nausea and vomiting
eject the contents of the stomach through the mouth
example: After drinking too much, the students vomited
The patient regurgitated the food we gave him last night

value.def: If you vomit, food and drink comes back up from your stomach and out through your mouth.

example.ex: Any product made from cow's  milk made him vomit...
example.tran: 任何乳制品都会让他呕吐。

example.ex: She began to vomit blood a few days before she died...
example.tran: 她临死前几天开始吐血。

example.ex: He vomited up all he had just eaten.
example.tran: 他把刚才吃下的所有东西都吐了出来。

example.ex: Nausea, diarrhoea, and vomiting may accompany migraine.
example.tran: 伴随偏头痛可能会出现恶心、腹泻和呕吐症状。

value.def: Vomit is partly digested food and drink that has come back up from someone's stomach and out through their mouth.
